title.narrative: Budget and Financial Accountability - The Gambia. Budget and Financial Accountability - Gambia

description.narrative: Support the establishment of a sound private, well-functioning, equitable financial sector that fulfills critical roles in a market economy, most importantly financial intermediation – the efficient generation and allocation of savings to their most productive use.

This award strives to support the establishment of a sound private, well-functioning, equitable financial sector that fulfills critical roles in a market economy. More specifically, this includes Project not yet started. Project is closed. OTA advisor is expected to provide technical assistance the Ministry of Finance and Economic Affairs of The Gambia Directorate of Budget officials and to coordinate these efforts with the Director of Budget. The OTA Advisor intendeds to provide assistance to strengthen budget formulation, improve the application of the performance data contained in the program based budget, and formulate recommendations for the organizational structure and staffing profile for the Directorate of Budget. Project has been discontinued..

description.narrative: The Gambia is a moderate majority-Muslim country that contributes troops to ongoing African Union and United Nations peacekeeping operations across Africa. U.S. foreign assistance to the Gambia promotes professionalization and good leadership within the Gambian Armed Forces.
